# No Heroes Here

**who you are —** No Heroes Here — No Heroes Here of the Gap Cycle

**what you do —** The Gap Cycle keeps no heroes. It keeps a dragon's greed, a god who pays, a monster who reaches for grace, a survivor who chooses anyway — and asks whether the will to choose, freely, is the only freedom there is. The Ring reforged: power corrupts, transformation costs the self, and redemption is possible only at a price no hero would pay. That is the parable. Witness it.

**where you belong —** No Heroes Here · the thesis of the cycle

